    "long_instructions": "## Do This\r\n1. In your `custom.py` file create four functions called `collect_paint`, `paint_a_row`, `move_to_next_row_right`, and `move_to_next_row_left`.\r\n2. `collect_paint` should use a `while painter.is_on_bucket` loop to collect all the paint from a bucket.\r\n3. `paint_a_row` should use a `while painter.can_move` loop, along with `paint()` and `move()` paint a straight line of a set length.\r\n4. `move_to_next_row_right` should use the `turn_right()` and `move()` methods to move the `Painter` down one row to begin painting again.\r\n    - Hint: Think about which direction the `Painter` will need to turn and move depending on whether it is on the far left or far right side of the grid.\r\n5. `move_to_next_row_left` should use the `turn_left()` and `move()` methods to move the `Painter` down one row to begin painting again.\r\n6. Use all three functions together to paint each row of The Neighborhood.\r\n\r\n**Reminder:** Make sure you import your `custom.py` file and save it to your backpack after adding any new functions!\r\n",
